MENUS

Welcome to West Bank Cafe, a classic NYC bistro serving up homemade Italian-American favorites alongside hearty American staples like burgers, steaks, and fresh fish. We proudly offer vegan and gluten-free options to suit every palate. Start your meal with our world-famous risotto balls, savor a satisfying entrée, and finish on a sweet note with a Chita Rivera-approved dessert. Whether you're dining for brunch, lunch, or dinner, we promise a delicious and friendly experience steps away from Broadway in the heart of Hell's Kitchen.

DINNER MENU
BRUNCH MENU

Downstairs at the WBC is one of New York's most intimate jewel box theatres, where stars like Joan Rivers, Stephen Sondheim, Nathan Lane, Ariana Grande, Andre DeShields, Jinx Monsoon, Aaron Sorkin, The Who, and thousands of others have worked and performed.

​

The Laurie Beechman Theatre has a rich history as a home for play development, cabaret, stand-up, concerts, drag, burlesque, sketch comedy, magic, and more!  

​

Join us in the newly redesigned theatre designed by the legendary David Rockwell.  Click the link for tix and info!

ABOUT US

Since 1978 The West Bank Cafe and The Laurie Beechman Theatre have been "A staple within the theatre community" (CBS News).  Located just steps away from Times Square and most Broadway theaters, The WBC has been a home for Hell's Kitchen residents, Broadway babies, and NYC visitors for almost five decades! Whether you're joining us for a pre-theater dinner, a post-show drink, a lunch meeting, or a party, The WBC is Broadway's ultimate neighborhood hangout.
